                            <comment id="14193747" author="pwendell" created="Sun, 2 Nov 2014 07:27:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adav&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adav&quot;&gt;adav&lt;/a&gt; just ran into an issue where a lot of our tests weren&apos;t properly cleaning SparkContext&apos;s and it was a huge pain. We could also log the callsite where a SparkContext is created, so if you try to create another one it actually tells you where the previous one was created and throws a helpful exception.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14199386" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 5 Nov 2014 23:43:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;JoshRosen&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
